                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2261h: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-13T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 13, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to International Consortium arrangement please use every effort to have
                    the Japanese Government agree and to send instructions and authority to act to
                    their representatives in Paris so that the meeting can be held on the 18th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
